SIMPLE: nicety
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Nicety
<hw>Ni"ce*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Niceties</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[OE.
<ets>nicet⟦eacute⟧</ets> foolishness.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
quality or state of being nice (in any of the senses of that
word.).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The miller smiled of her <qex>nicety</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Delicacy or exactness of perception; minuteness of
observation or of discrimination; precision.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A delicate expression, act, mode of treatment,
distinction, or the like; a minute distinction.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The fineness and <qex>niceties</qex> of words.</q>
<rj><qau>Locke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>To a nicety</b></col>, <cd>with great exactness or
accuracy.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Niche</ent>⟦br⟧
